eu.ehri.extension.base

Class AbstractAccessibleResource<E extends Accessible>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.ehri.extension.base.AbstractResource
      • eu.ehri.extension.base.AbstractAccessibleResource<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the specific Accessible derived class
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    TxCheckedResource
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AnnotationResource, AuthoritativeSetResource, ContentTypeResource, CountryResource, CvocConceptResource, DocumentaryUnitResource, GenericResource, GroupResource, HistoricalAgentResource, LinkResource, RepositoryResource, SystemEventResource, UserProfileResource, VersionResource, VirtualUnitResource, VocabularyResource

    public class AbstractAccessibleResource<E extends Accessible>
extends AbstractResource
    Handle CRUD operations on Accessible's by using the eu.ehri.project.views.Views class generic code. Resources for specific entities can extend this class.

      • createItem

        public <T extends Accessible> javax.ws.rs.core.Response createItem(Bundle entityBundle,
                                                                   List<String> accessorIds,
                                                                   AbstractAccessibleResource.Handler<T> handler,
                                                                   Api scopedApi,
                                                                   Class<T> otherCls)
                                                            throws PermissionDenied,
                                                                   ValidationError,
                                                                   DeserializationError
        Create an instance of the 'entity' in the database
        Type Parameters:
        T - the generic type of class T
        Parameters:
        entityBundle - a bundle of item data 'id' fields)
        accessorIds - a list of accessors who can initially view this item
        handler - a callback function that allows additional operations to be run on the created object after it is initialised but before the response is generated. This is useful for adding relationships to the new item.
        scopedApi - the Api instance to use to create the item. This allows callers to override the scope used.
        otherCls - the class of the created item.
        Returns:
        the response of the create request, the 'location' will contain the url of the newly created instance.
        Throws:
        PermissionDenied
        ValidationError
        DeserializationError
